							<br>
							<h2>Lumen<br>
							<font size="2"><img src="../images/spacer.gif" alt="" height="5" width="20" border="0">(Receive the light and pass it on.)</font><br></h2>
							<b>Voicing:</b> unison chant, with 3 part canon<br>
							<b>Text:</b> Latin aphorisms (Anonymous)<br>
							<b>Duration:</b> varies<br>
							<b>Commissioned by:</b> Waupaca High School Treble Clef 2012<br>
							<b>Published by:</b> Abbie Betinis Music Co., AB-071-01<br>
							<b>Order online:</b> <a href="../order_form.html">Online order form</a><br>
							<br>
							<span class="works-headers">PROGRAM NOTE</span>
							<div class="works-body">
							<img id="float_left" src="../images/works--lumen.jpg" height="204" width="139" border="0">These two Latin aphorisms are of unknown origin, but since the first (<em>Lumen accipe et imperti</em>) is a motto for many schools around the world, I wanted to make the music sound like one part is "teaching" the next part.  I also imagined the light growing a little bit stronger each time it passes from singer to singer, so I started with small intervals that gradually expand into larger leaps and long scales.<br>
							<div id="poem">
							<br>
								<table>
									<tr>
										<td>
										<span id="poem_title">Lumen</span><br>
										Lumen accipe et imperti. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br>
										Do ut des.<br>
										<br>
										<br>
										<br>
										</td>
										<td>
										<span id="poem_title"><em>(Light)</em></span><br>
										<em>Receive the light and pass it on.<br>
										I give that you may give.</em><br>
										<br>
										<span id="poem_credit"><align="left">This text and translation are in the public domain.</span> 
										<br>
										<br>
										</td>
									</tr>
								</table> 
							</div>
							</div>
